Project Manager
Roles and Responsibilities
 Oversee, manage multiple vendors and external providers of ICT services, work with team members from application and infra teams, to deliver project on time and within budget;
 Project Management (Scope, Budget and Schedule) including regular management reporting for maintenance and/or development projects;
 Conduct requirements workshop to gather user requirements and analyses business processes to provide clear analysis and documentation of the problems and proposed;
 Ensure that projects are executed based on the project plan to meet identified business needs, within agreed parameters of cost, duration and quality;
 Participate and contribute in project activities such as Requirement Gathering, User Acceptance Testing, Training & Implementation;
 Review project deliverables. e.g. functional specifications, system test plan & results, user guide, operation manual;
 Plan and perform user acceptance testing;
 Assess service requests... for enhancements and maintenance of systems;
 Ensure Service Level Agreements for projects and incidents are met;
 Identify potential project risks and its implication to the organisation and to recommend mitigating measures to manage the risks;
 Understand the IT management policy, quality management policy and security guidelines to ensure the development processes, procedures and system are designed to comply with these policies and guidelines; and
 Manage and resolve day-to-day IT related issues pertaining to application, infrastructure or security, to facilitate smooth running of daily operations
Knowledge and Skills
 Tertiary education in Computer/Computer Science or Electronics Engineering or Information Technology or equivalent preferred.
 Advantageous to have Project Management Certification or equivalent.
 Relevant working experience as Project Manager/Scrum Master in at least 2 Agile/full project development life cycle.
 Relevant experience in web-based development and mobile IT projects.
 Working experience in .Net/J2EE applications, iOS/Android for mobile apps is preferred.
 Familiarity with governance, adoption and training in RPA in enterprise IT environments.
 Working experience in government environment and familiarity with the statistical and corporate systems will be beneficial
 Work experience and strong troubleshooting skills in resolving application, infrastructure (including desktop, server, network) and security related issues in a government environment is preferred.
 Strong analytical, conceptualisation and problem-solving skills.
 Ability to take a broad, strategic perspective as well as drill deep to understand business needs and challenges.
 Results and customer oriented.

