An excellent opportunity for a Scrum Master who has rich experience in managing projects to join one of the leading Financial Institutions.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Bachelor Degree in Computer Science or Information Systems disciplines;
• At least 3 years as a Scrum Master or Agile Consultant or a Project Manager managing a Agile project;
• At least 10 years of System or Software engineering with strong handson background in software development;
• Good experience with Agile development methodology such as Scrum and KanBan;
• Excellent ability to understand business objectives and overcome business needs and challenges;
• Demonstrated capability in testing,automation, development and project management;
• Ability to work independently, manage stress and multitask in a fastpaced environment;
• Excellent stakeholder management skills;
• Strong communication, presentation, documentation and negotiation skills.

Desirable Skill(s)
• First Level Scrum Master certification (CSM, PSM I);
•... Second level Scrum Master certification (CSM, PSM II).

Responsibilities
• Responsible for the software delivery of Technology projects using Agile Software Development Methodology;
• Plan and manage the risks, issues, costs and schedule following the Agile framework and principles;
• Work closely with the Business Users / Product Owners in Sprint/Release planning to prioritize the product features and releases;
• Drive the adoption and rollout of Agile design and engineering practices which include test driven development, continuous integration and release automation (CI/RA) as well as automated testing;
• Lead the Project / Scrum team in design methods and principles, adopting a standard for issue and risk management as well as the management of the product backlog and inventory;
• Provide guidance and direction to the team to ensure effective and continuous delivery pipeline with the appropriate level of automation
